<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Create Mist Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        Creates a decorative fog or mist effect at the Event Point location.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What Create Mist Does
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Create Mist</Bold> Event Point creates a decorative layer of fog or mist at the
        Event Point location. It is used to add atmosphere to a scene rather than to create an NPC,
        item, trap, objective, or mission rule.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        This Event Point is very simple. It has no type-specific properties. The main things you
        control are where the mist appears, when it is created, and how it fits into the scene.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_mist_overview.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Simple summary:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Create Mist places a fog/mist effect at the Event Point position.
                    It has no type-specific fields; placement and trigger setup are the important parts.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- ADDING -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Adding a Create Mist Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        To add a mist effect, click <Bold>Add</Bold> in the Event Points panel, select
        <Bold>Create Mist</Bold> from the Event Point type list, and click <Bold>OK</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The <Bold>Edit EventPoint</Bold> window opens with the standard common properties and trigger
        settings. There are no extra Create Mist-specific fields to configure.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_mist_add_type.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- COMMON PROPERTIES -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Common Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Create Mist uses the standard Event Point common properties: index number, Event Point type,
        letter group, colour, position, trigger settings, and listening mode.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The index number and Event Point type are automatic. Letter group and colour can be set
        however you prefer. For scene effects, it can be useful to keep decorative Event Points in a
        consistent group or colour so they are easy to filter and identify later.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_mist_common_properties.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Position
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>position</Bold> controls where the mist appears. Use
        <Bold>Select Position on Map</Bold> to place the Event Point visually in the viewport.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Place the mist where it supports the atmosphere of the map. For example, you might place it
        around drains, alleys, water, dark industrial areas, vents, sewer entrances, night scenes, or
        any location where low fog makes the scene feel more dramatic.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_mist_position.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- NO TYPE-SPECIFIC PROPERTIES -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Type-Specific Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Create Mist has <Bold>no type-specific properties</Bold>. There is no mist type, colour,
        density, radius, speed, height, count, or item/object selection to configure in this Event
        Point.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        If the mist does not appear as expected, check the common properties first: position, trigger,
        and listening mode.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Important:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Create Mist is controlled through common Event Point setup only.
                    The visual result depends on where it is placed and when it is triggered.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- TRIGGER SETTINGS -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Trigger Settings
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        For normal decorative use, mist is usually created when the mission starts. The typical setup
        is:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Triggered By:</Bold> None / Game Starts.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Listening Mode:</Bold> Active.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        This makes the mist appear immediately and remain available as part of the scene.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_mist_trigger_settings.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Triggered Mist
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Although None / Active is the typical setup, Create Mist can also be placed behind mission
        logic if you want the mist to appear later. For example, mist could appear after the player
        enters an area, after a switch is used, after a trap activates, or after a scripted sequence
        changes the atmosphere of the scene.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        In that case, use the trigger that matches the desired mission event, such as
        <Bold>Dependency</Bold>, <Bold>Player Enters Radius</Bold>, <Bold>Switch</Bold>, or another
        appropriate trigger.
    </Paragraph>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- PRACTICAL USES -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Practical Uses
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Atmospheric Night Scene</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Place mist in alleys, streets, or open areas to make a night mission feel colder, darker, or
        more cinematic.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Industrial Area</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Use mist around factories, vents, pipes, drains, or machinery areas to suggest steam, heat,
        pollution, or poor visibility.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Sewer or Water Area</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Place mist near water, sewer entrances, tunnels, drains, or underground areas to make the
        environment feel damp and heavy.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Cinematic Scene Dressing</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Use mist as background dressing for cutscenes, camera sequences, important NPC encounters, or
        dramatic mission moments.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Area Reveal</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Trigger mist later through dependency logic if you want the atmosphere to change after an
        event, such as opening a gate, activating machinery, or entering a restricted area.
    </Paragraph>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- WORKFLOW -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Basic Create Mist Workflow
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Click <Bold>Add</Bold> in the Event Points panel.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Select <Bold>Create Mist</Bold> and click <Bold>OK</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Choose a letter group and colour that fits your mission organisation.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>Select Position on Map</Bold> to place the mist where it should appear.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Triggered By</Bold> to <Bold>None / Game Starts</Bold> for normal decorative mist.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Listening Mode</Bold> to <Bold>Active</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Click <Bold>OK</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Save and test the mission to confirm the mist appears in the correct place.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- TROUBLESHOOTING -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Troubleshooting
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The mist does not appear</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the Create Mist Event Point exists in the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the Event Point trigger is firing.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>For simple decorative use, test with <Bold>Triggered By: None / Game Starts</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm <Bold>Listening Mode</Bold> is set to <Bold>Active</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the Event Point is placed somewhere visible in the map area.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The mist appears in the wrong place</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Move the Event Point using <Bold>Select Position on Map</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check the X/Z coordinate values if the marker was placed manually.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Test again in game after moving it.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The mist appears too early or too late</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check the trigger used by the Create Mist Event Point.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>None / Game Starts</Bold> if it should exist from the beginning.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>Dependency</Bold> or another trigger if it should appear later in the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Final note:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Create Mist is mostly decorative. Use it to improve atmosphere, guide mood, or dress a scene.
                    It does not replace objective, trap, item, or camera Event Points.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

</FlowDocument>